itemDescription: Archdeacon of St Albans in the Church of England from 2003 until 2007

wikipedia_page.main: Helen Margaret Cunliffe (born 1954) is a British Anglican priest who was Archdeacon of St Albans from 2003 to 2007.

response: * Helen Cunliffe, later Archdeacon of St Albans, served as the church's first female vicar from 1994 to 1995, having been deacon-in-charge since 1989.
